    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix Viterbi Test Compilation and Runtime Issues\n\n### Summary\nThe viterbi_test.c file in the PHY/CODING/TESTBENCH directory had multiple compilation and runtime issues that prevented the main function from executing properly. The test was failing to build due to incorrect header file includes and missing function declarations. Additionally, at runtime it would segfault when trying to call non-existent CRC functions and viterbi decoder functions with mismatched parameters.\n\nThe root cause was incorrect header references, usage of undefined crc24 function instead of the available crc24a, and calling phy_viterbi_dot11_sse2 with wrong parameter count. These issues have been resolved by updating the header includes, replacing crc24 calls with crc24a, and using the correct phy_viterbi_dot11 function.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/TESTBENCH/viterbi_test.c`: Fixed header includes to use correct file paths\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/TESTBENCH/viterbi_test.c`: Replaced undefined crc24 function calls with crc24a\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/TESTBENCH/viterbi_test.c`: Changed phy_viterbi_dot11_sse2 to phy_viterbi_dot11 to match parameter count\n"
}